Danisco takes over Norwegian package firm . Danish food and drinks group Danisco A / S said on Wednesday its packaging division ' s Danisco Flamingo unit was taking over Norwegian packaging firm Monoplast from Norway ' s Naering Invest for an undisclosed sum . The acquisition , which is to adopt the name of Danisco Monoplast , employs 20 staff with an annual turnover of around 25 million Norwegian crowns , Danisco said in a statement . - - Chris Follett , Copenhagen newsroom + 45 - 33969652 
